      <section eId="sec_36_38_3">
        <num>36-38-3</num>
        <content>
          <p>Whenever and as soon as the sinking fund of any municipal corporation has been invested in municipal, county, state, or federal government bonds as required by Code Section 36-38-1, the officer or officers of such municipal corporation charged with the custody of its funds and securities shall proceed forthwith to have the securities in which such funds are so invested registered in the name of the municipal corporation, provided such bonds by their terms under the conditions of their issue are capable of being registered in the name of the owner.</p>
          <p>(Ga. L. 1910, p. 100, ยง 4; Code 1933, ยง 87-704.)</p>
